38 //
39 // Base class for all environment models, providing separate collision check
40 // functions for each type of tracking error bound. All environments are
41 // boxes in 3D space.
42 //
44 
45 #ifndef FASTRACK_ENVIRONMENT_ENVIRONMENT_H
46 #define FASTRACK_ENVIRONMENT_ENVIRONMENT_H

48 #include <fastrack/bound/box.h>
49 #include <fastrack/utils/types.h>

51 #include <ros/ros.h>

53 namespace fastrack {
54 namespace environment {
55 
56 using bound::Box;
57 
58 class Environment {
59 public:
60  virtual ~Environment() {}
61 
62  // Initialize from a ROS NodeHandle.
63  bool Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
64 
65  // Derived classes must provide a collision checker which returns true if
66  // and only if the provided position is a valid collision-free configuration.
67  // Provide a separate collision check for each type of tracking error bound.
68  virtual bool IsValid(const Vector3d& position, const Box& bound) const = 0;
69 
70  // Utility for checking multiple positions.
71  bool AreValid(const std::vector<Vector3d>& positions, const Box& bound) const;
72 
73  // Derived classes must have some sort of visualization through RViz.
74  virtual void Visualize(const ros::Publisher& pub,
75  const std::string& frame) const = 0;
76 
77 protected:
78  explicit Environment()
79  : initialized_(false) {}
80 
81  // Load parameters. This may be overridden by derived classes if needed
82  // (they should still call this one via Environment::LoadParameters).
83  virtual bool LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
84 
85  // Upper and lower bounds.
86  Vector3d lower_;
87  Vector3d upper_;
88 
89  // Naming and initialization.
90  std::string name_;
91  bool initialized_;
92 }; //\class Environment

94 } //\namespace environment
95 } //\namespace fastrack
